<TITLE> SQ Chy warns BNP 'reformists' of tough action </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, August 1 (bdnews24.com)Veteran BNP leader Salauddin Quader Chowdhury MP warned of a similar fate for his party's one-time 'reformists' after Awami League, in forming its new committee earlier in the week, sidelined long-time party heavyweights who were seen to take the part of the past caretaker government in trying to bring about 'party reforms'. Chowdhury praised AL president Sheikh Hasina on her new committee. "The new Awami League committee reflects the bravery of the party president." "The situation will be even tougher for the so-called BNP's 'reformists'. Proper steps will be initiated against them in time," Chowdhury warned. bd
